summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsNARS Laguna Bronzing Powder creates instant warmth and a long-wearing natural looking glow, in nine talc-free shades.
details: DetailsBenefitsNine bronze shades can be used to contour, sculpt, or enhance the look of skinFinely milled, talc-free powders blend color seamlessly, and translucent micro-spheres smooth skin texture for a perfected complexionSilky pigments deliver instant, long-lasting warmth with all-day comfortFeaturesTalc-freeNatural finishLong-lastingFor all skin tonesItem 2608918How To UseFor fair and light complexions, select a Laguna Bronzing Powder with a neutral or warm undertone. For deeper complexions, select one with red or neutral undertones to enhance depth and dimension.To create soft, all-over warmth, swirl Laguna Bronzing Powder onto the apples of cheeks, blending outwards and upwards along the cheekbones. Sweep a small amount across the forehead and bridge of the nose for an additional sunkissed look.For a contoured effect, apply Laguna Bronzing Powder one to two shades deeper than the natural skin tone in the hollows of the cheekbones and jawline.Use remaining pigment to blend onto the neck and dÃ©colletÃ© to prevent lines of demarcation.Apply in a circular motion, continuously buffing and blending, to avoid harsh lines.IngredientsSynthetic Fluorphlogopite, Mica, Ethylhexyl Palmitate, Silica, Zinc Stearate, Dimethicone, Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Zinc Oxide, Sorbitan Sesquiisostearate, Tocopherol, Isopropyl Titanium Triisostearate, Chlorphenesin, [+/-(May Contain/Peut Contenir): Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891), Ultramarines (CI 77007)]Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

faceoff_positive.headline: Absolute fav bronzer

faceoff_negative.comments: I got the shade Laguna 02 because it's meant to be the same as the original Laguna but it's not. The only good thing is that it's still buttery/smooth.     1st thing that's different is it doesn't have as much finely milled shimmer so this reformulated version seems less glowy which is a fairly big let down as I loved it because of the radiance it gave.     The bigger issue I have is the change in undertone. I'm a medium depth with a golden-olive hue. The reason I loves Laguna was because it leaned more yellow/green. In the swatches of the new shades, Laguna 02 does seem olive hued however compared to the previous one I bought a few months back, the new talc-free version has a touch more red to it which doesn't work for me. The original laguna was person, the depth only being a couple shades darker than me made prevented it from looking orange but the reformulation just has a little too much red and makes the overall color pull more orange on me so I definitely would not buy this again unfortunately
faceoff_negative.headline: Undertone change
